text: This is just a review of the audiobook plan. I appreciate the addition of audiobooks. title: Cache takes up a LOT
text:
Recent releases require the app to build up an enormous amount of Cache files ‚Äî system files that take up a lot of space on your device.

After about a week the app is over 5GB and growing. The easy fix is to frequently clear cache files from the Settings panel. This will merely take the app down to 1GB, and it will build back up quickly over time.

The overall fix is to delete the entire app and reinstall about once a month.

This is the best music streaming app by far so hopefully they‚Äôll get this cache issue worked out quickly.

title: No spacial no hi-rez audio
text:
Although the music discovery and recommendations are good, Spotify  is lacking in spatial audio, it has none compared with Apple Music.  In the past, one could utilize the BOOM audio app with Spotify to capture a spatial sense.   Unfortunately, the Boom app no longer works with Spotify music. I suspect Spotify would have to allow an API for the Boom app to work.  it‚Äôs too bad‚Ä¶.

Spodify‚Äôs audio Fidelity is, at best, CD quality; so if you want Hi-Rez audio, use Apple or Amazon Music

title: Premium is worth it
text:
I‚Äôve used Apple Music, Spotify free and premium. Apple Music gets the job done, but Spotify makes finding new favorites super easy. Obviously the experience of listening to a song is the same regardless of the app, but I love all the extra goodies Spotify comes with, like DJ and smart shuffle, and the new ‚Äúmusic TikTok‚Äù type thing they started doing where you can listen to snippets of songs from an album to see if you wanna listen to the whole song(s). 

One more thing, a premium subscription is worth its weight in gold. You can listen with Spotify for free which can‚Äôt be said for most of the other top apps, but they throw in ads every four or five songs, you can‚Äôt cherry pick songs/ you have to listen on shuffle and it shuffles in other songs that you may or may not like. 

If you get Spotify, get premium too. And you should 100% download Spotify
